<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Glyceria</i> ×<i>occidentalis</i> is dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Eleocharis</i> <i>macrostachya</i>, <i>Eleocharis</i> <i>parishii</i>, <i>Limnanthes</i> <i>striata</i> and <i>Potamogeton</i> <i>gramineus</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Wet depressions, ditch bottoms, streamsides, lakeshores, backwater sites, pools, and swales. Soils are seasonally to permanently saturated. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Glyceria occidentalis</i> as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

		
